  "texts": [
    "In contrast, time-series data, such as ECG and EEG records, are necessary to monitor physiological function changes over time.",
    "The dominance of images as the primary data type can be attributed to the increasing use of medical imaging techniques in clinical practice and research.",
    "With the advancements in imaging technology, clinicians can now obtain high-quality images that provide detailed information about the structure and function of various organs and tissues.",
    "Additionally, numerical data can capture continuous measurements such as blood pressure, heart rate, and body temperature.",
    "In contrast, categorical data can capture non-continuous measurements such as gender, age, and medical history."
